cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the statistical physics of random codes and their behavior at finite temperatures, which is closely related to information theory and coding theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the phase diagram of the decoder, which involves the study of complex systems and their behavior, making cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses concepts from statistical mechanics and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between the random coding exponents and the statistical physics of random codes, which involves the study of control systems and their behavior, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
